=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tzaroth:</span><hr size=1> About Iksar, Erudite Heretics and outsiders...<br>
<br>
Well, here's my thoughts, opinians and observations on it, you can do with them what you will or ignore them completely. *smiles* <br>
<br>
Iksar society is structured such that everyone is born to a caste and is assigned a job, the entire society has a clear heirarchy of command and everyones place in it is very clear. Essentially, they literally have NO system to accomodate outsiders or visitors. Who would the visitors take orders from? What would they be allowed to do and not to do? If they can be orderd around by anyone, they essentially become slaves once they enter and will never leave, while if nobody can order them around they have more rights then an Iksar, and that naturally just wouldn't work.<br>
<br>
Iksar have absolutely no way, within the structure of their society, to accomodate visitors or outsiders. I tried very hard to think of an excuse, but outsiders being within Iksar cities is essentially completely unRPable for the Iksar. The exception being that they are slaves, of course. <br>
<br>
The other way would be for an outsider to join a caste, but I honestly don't see Iksar letting outsiders join a caste of theirs. It'd cause alot of political problems (Distrust would start to grow, alot of Iksar would think the Empire is desperate, stuff like that), and there just isn't too much reason for it. Not to mention to join a caste means you would be treated equally, and I can't see Iksar ever treating outsiders equally. (Although maybe they could make a special rank that is lower then even the lowest Iksar rank just for an outsider?) <br>
<br>
The relationship I see between Iksar and Erudites, well, I won't speak for the Erudites, but I see Iksar as essentially considering them as disgracing Cazic-Thule's name, worshiping him completely wrong, etc. After all, if they were true followers of Thule, they'd accept that the Iksar were his chosen and bow down and willingly become slaves. Since they do not, they are blasphemers who abuse Cazic-Thule's name. <br>
<br>
And of course, Cazic-Thule really DOES favor the Iksar over any other race. *smirks* <br>
<br>
Anyway, hope that information is of some use. Have fun and good gaming to you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 389<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/7/02 11:07:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2763.topic&index=29>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/btk120/antoin.gif width=68 height=146></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> *nods at Daemonifuge*</span><hr size=1> *bonks self* So that's who you are!<br>
