<br>
I'm very glad to see so much interest in this thread and Heretics in general, especially from some familiar names. Although my hours can be very late, I'd be happy to speak with any young Heretics in game, so shoot me a tell if you see me around.<br>
<br>
For myself, my knowledge of the NPC background surrounding Odus is very incomplete. I really need to take Antoin's suggestion and roll up a Loyalist on another server. Because I didn't want to risk getting stuck in constant contradictions with the background already in place, I have used my own NPCs and background for the basis of Fyanna, and then tried to incorporate elements from Norrath and in-game characters as they fit. As I've said elsewhere, nearly everything about Fyanna is a melting pot of references to anime, horror stories, David Lynch movies, and other games. Its all just for fun as a tip of the hat to things that I have found neat. That being said, she still adheres very strictly to the Orderly Evil alignment and upholds the principles of the Fell Knights.<br>
<br>
Fyanna is a member of the shadowy organization known as Seele, which operates from within the Hole under Paineel. The motives and goals of Seele are not known to any outside of it, although its influence can be indirectly felt throughout Norrath's history. They manipulate events on Odus and use the High Council of Paineel as a front for their activities. Seele follows a strict Timetable in its efforts to complete the Project, which is often linked to various key phrases in intercepted reports. Some of these phrases include the Bakumatsu, Human Instrumentality, the Black Lodge, and the Shinma.<br>
<br>
Fyanna's position in Seele is as the Handmaiden of Pain, a title that was awarded to her following the completion of the Riot of Blood. She was raised from infancy within the temple of Nerv to be used as a living weapon, and her entire upbringing and training were centered around that. As such, she has little or no sense of self, and follows her orders unquestioningly. Recently she was assigned to establish relations with the League of Shadows, where she performs duties as a Hitokiri, or house assassin. She has secret additional orders regarding several figures that are listed in the Project's schedule. Some of these figures know who they are...some don't.<br>
<br>
A recent relevation from Captain Nolouj shows that Fyanna is in fact the daughter of Meralith, and thus Antoin's niece. This information has been kept secret by Seele for various reasons, partly because of their involvement with the circumstances surrounding the incident, and partly out of concern that Fyanna's mental state might become unstable should she discover the truth. There is a great deal of mystery in what might actually be imbued beneath the surface of the Handmaiden's conciousness, and Seele will not tolerate a loss of their investment. <p><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/anime4/fyanna/snk_kojirou3.gif><br><b>Fyanna</b><br>Fell Knight of Thule<br>Hitokiri to the League of Shadows<br><i>There can be no salvation without destruction,</i><br><i>no hope this side of death..</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhaldrim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haldrim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/10/02 3:03:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2763.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well, well...</span><hr size=1> I have come full circle.  Hueth returns.  Lost at sea for forsaking his Diety, the power and wrath of the Oceanlord flows once again in his viens.<br>
<br>
I say this:  Good and Evil are trivial to one who holds the power of the tides.  Both Heretic and Loyalist are, above all, Erudites.  The misguided humans, the tree-dwarfs, the rock-loving clock-makers, the bearded Brellites, the slow witted swamp dwellers, and the indigo skinned mutants all have thier place...  under us.<br>
<br>
I will seek out my brothers, sisters, and cousins.  You too, sned word if there are matters of which we need to speak.<br>
<br>
Hueth<br>
